   <title type="text">Online Prepublication: Babylonian Chronicles of the Hellenistic Period</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/chron00.html">Mesopotamian Chronicles</a><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/a/1/mesopotamia/jerusalem_597.jpg"><img alt="Babylonian cuneiform tablet, mentioning the fall of Jerusalem in 597 BCE. British Museum, London (Britain). Photo Marco Prins." src="http://www.livius.org/a/2/mesopotamia/jerusalem_597_s.JPG" style="border: 2px solid; height: 195px; width: 150px;" title="Babylonian cuneiform tablet, mentioning the fall of Jerusalem in 597 BCE. British Museum, London (Britain). Photo Marco Prins." /></a>                                                                                                 </div><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Cuneiform tablet mentioning       the capture of Jerusalem in&nbsp;597 (<a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/abc5/jerusalem.html">text</a>; British Museum)</span></div><br /><br /><i>Babylonian Chronicles of the Hellenistic Period</i> (= <b><i>BCHP</i></b>)<br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;">....is being prepared by Irving Finkel of the British Museum (London) and <a href="http://www.let.vu.nl/nl/organisatie-van-de-faculteit/wetenschappelijk-personeel/medewerkers-alfabetisch/medewerkers-l-s/prof-dr-r-j-van-der-spek/index.asp">Bert van der Spek</a> of the Free University of Amsterdam (Holland).<a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/chron00.html#een">*</a> Their results <a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/chron00.html">are presented here</a> for the first time, so you will also find scholarly editions of the texts, which presuppose some knowledge of the Akkadian language. This online-publication is intended to invite suggestions for better readings, comments and interpretations (go <a href="mailto:rj.vander.spek@let.vu.nl">here</a>to contact Van der Spek).                                                                                                                Below, you will find an overview of chronicles, more or less in their chronological order. For those who are unfamiliar with the subject but are interested, the "reader's editions" ought to be accessible. These are simplified translations. After reading a bit about the <a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/reading.html">conventions of publication</a>, the "scholarly editions" ought to be accessible too.&nbsp;       </span></blockquote>All Babylonian Chronicles are presented in translation at <a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/chron00.html">Mesopotamian Chronicles</a>, courtesy of <a href="http://www.livius.org/">Livius</a>, with the new editions of texts to be included in BCHP presented in scholarly editions. The most recently completed one being an <a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/bchp-bagayasha/bchp-bagayasha_c1.html">Astronomical Diary Concerning Bagayasha and Timotheos</a>.&nbsp;<br /><br />The list of chronicles completed so far includes:<br /><br /><blockquote><table border="0"><tbody><tr bgcolor="#ccffff"><td><span style="font-size: x-small;">ABC 8</span></td>                             <td><span style="font-size: x-small;">CM 29</span></td>                             <td style="width: 103px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">BCHP 1</span></td>                             <td style="width: 314px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/aj-al/alexander/alexander00.html">Alexander</a>chronicle</span></td>                             <td style="width: 122px;"><br /><br /><center><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/bchp-alexander/alexander_01.html">Scholarly edition</a></span></center>                            </td>                             <td style="width: 73px;"><br /><br /><center><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/bchp-alexander/alexander_06.html#alternative">Translation</a></span></center>                            </td>                          </tr><tr bgcolor="#ccffff">                            <td><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></td>                             <td><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></td>                             <td style="width: 103px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">BCHP 2</span></td>                             <td style="width: 314px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">Alexander and <a href="http://www.livius.org/ap-ark/arabia/arabia.html">Arabia</a>chronicle</span></td>                             <td style="width: 122px;"><br /><br /><center><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/bchp-arabia/arabia_01.html">Scholarly edition</a></span></center>                            </td>                             <td style="width: 73px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></td>                          </tr><tr bgcolor="#ccffff">                            <td><span style="font-size: x-small;">ABC 10</span></td>                             <td><span style="font-size: x-small;">CM 30</span></td>                             <td style="width: 103px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">BCHP 3</span></td>                             <td style="width: 314px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/di-dn/diadochi/diadochi.htm">Diadochi</a>chronicle</span></td>                             <td style="width: 122px;"><br /><br /><center><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/cg-cm/chronicles/bchp-diadochi/diadochi_01.html">Scholarly edition</a></span></center>                            </td>                             <td style="width: 73px;"><br /><br /><center><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.livius.org/di-dn/diadochi/diadochi_t13.html">Translation</a></span></center>                            </td>                          </tr><tr bgcolor="